# Git & PR workflow

When shipping code for this repo, **do not commit or push directly to `main`**. Use a feature branch and pull request every time.

## Workflow

1. Create a branch: `git checkout -b feat/short-description`
2. Make changes and verify (build/lint as appropriate)
3. Before commit, check: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log --oneline -5`
4. Stage only relevant files — **never** `.env`, secrets, or `server/assets/template.docx`
5. Commit with a message focused on **why**
6. Push: `git push -u origin HEAD`
7. Open PR: `gh pr create` with Summary + Test plan
8. Merge: `gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch`
9. Sync local: `git checkout main && git pull`

## When the user asks to "commit", "push", or "ship"

Default to the full workflow above unless they explicitly say commit-only or push-to-main.

Return the **PR URL** when done.

## Never

- Force-push to `main`
- Commit `.env` or credential files
- Skip PR for multi-file or feature work on `main`
